Introduction to Logistic Regression

The training session began with an introduction to Logistic Regression, a supervised Machine Learning algorithm used for solving classification problems. Learned that unlike Linear Regression, which predicts continuous numerical values, Logistic Regression predicts categorical outcomes such as Yes/No, True/False, Spam/Not Spam, or Disease/No Disease.

The trainer explained that Logistic Regression estimates the probability of an event occurring and classifies data into predefined categories based on that probability. It is one of the most widely used classification algorithms due to its simplicity, efficiency, and interpretability.

