Difference Between Linear Regression and Logistic Regression

Compared Linear Regression with Logistic Regression.

Learned that:

Linear Regression predicts continuous numerical values.
Logistic Regression predicts categorical outcomes.
Linear Regression uses a straight-line equation.
Logistic Regression uses the Sigmoid Function to produce probabilities between 0 and 1.

Discussed situations where each algorithm should be applied.

Understanding the Sigmoid Function

Received a detailed explanation of the Sigmoid Function, which is the core of Logistic Regression.

Learned that the sigmoid function transforms any numerical value into a probability ranging from 0 to 1.

Studied how:

Probability close to 1 indicates the positive class.
Probability close to 0 indicates the negative class.

Discussed the role of threshold values (typically 0.5) in assigning class labels.

